        %p.medium
          Let's build better
          %em civic
          software, together.
        %p.medium
          Civic innovation everywhere depends on open-source, civic software that is easy to adopt and improve. For civic hacking to have maximum impact, the whole ecosystem should be well documented, clean and fork-ready.
        %p.medium
          So before we build the next big thing, let's rally together this summer and whip our collective repos into shape! Let's empty our issues lists, merge some pull requests and make it so anyone anywhere can re-use our code. There will be prizes and plenty of fun.
        %p.medium
          We encourage local Brigades to choose repos to hack on collectively, and we're also looking for a few repos to feature for our national community to work together on.
